                <h1>Kara Walker: Powerful Art Addressing Race and History</h1>
                <p>Kara Walker is a prominent American artist known for her provocative silhouettes that explore themes of race, gender, and history. Through her cutting paper forms and installations, Walker confronts the complexities of the African American experience, inviting viewers to engage with often uncomfortable truths about the past and present social dynamics.</p>
